You can tell the game is in very early stages but has promise. Super Boring at the moment. Ideas for improvement: More attributes: Warmth. Energy. So you have to stay warm and sleep to restore energy. Going in water and walking outdoors at night reduces warmth. Special areas with Hard enemies but special rsre loot. Like a cave or something.. Ability to name containers to help with organisations. Different sized crates. Different types of 3d printers which produce different level items at different speeds. For example, you need a tribal 3d printer to craft camp fires. Weather effects. Emotional effects. For example, being in the rain lowers warmth and happiness, eating certain foods boost happiness. Happiness affects build speed, rare loot drop rate and damage resistance. Another idea would be random events that happen.. For example, a meteor crashes and you can mine it for rare ore, or a huge alien monster appears and you can kill it for great food and maybe some loot. My last suggestion is instead of having different laser miner guns. You have one, but there are loads of different mods, in a skill tree (like the game deadspace). You craft the mods and attach using a specific 3d printer.

content: Really ambitious project that I can applaud the developers in producing. Upon first impression everything is great with settings on max getting 60+ fps on Huawei mate 10 which was surprising. Can I suggest maybe a setting on reducing the bending on the sides of the display? Similar to like a reverse fisheye the center of the screen has a "flat" view but is distorted(more like picture stretch and curved) on the left and right side of the screen slightly. Is noticable when looking around in circles.
